Michigan is a state in the northern part of the United States. It is divided into two parts; the upper and lower peninsulas. Lakes Michigan and Huron separate the two, but a bridge connects the two. People who live in the lower peninsula are called trolls, while the others are called UPers.
Michigan is the only state that borders four Great Lakes: Lakes Michigan, Huron, Superior, and Erie.
Michigan is a major manufacturer of automobiles, and GM headquarters is in Detroit. The landscape of the lower peninsula is mainly flat, so agriculture is very prominent there. The upper peninsula has a sufficient amount of copper ore and timber.
Michigan is also famous for its sand dunes. There is also a legend about it. One day, a ravaging fire broke out in Wisconsin, so a mother bear and her cubs swam Lake Michigan. The two cubs drowned, and formed the Manitou Islands. The mother bear reached land, but waited for her cubs. She waited so long,she became a sand dune. Other Michiganian legends have been made into children's books.